<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<div class="call-to-action">
<p>You may be able to claim compensation through the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/windrush-compensation-scheme">Windrush Compensation Scheme</a> if you suffered a loss because you could not demonstrate your lawful right to live in the UK.</p>
</div>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>If you are applying from outside the UK you must use the <a rel="external" href="https://visas-immigration.service.gov.uk/apply-visa-type/windrush">online application form</a>.
<br></br><br></br>
You must use the paper form above ‘Windrush scheme application (UK)’ if you are applying inside the UK.</p>
</div>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>You can read our <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/windrush-scheme-support-in-urgent-and-exceptional-circumstances">policy on how support can be provided to members of the Windrush cohort with an urgent, exceptional need</a> in advance of a Windrush compensation scheme.</p>
</div>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>Have your say in shaping the Windrush compensation scheme by <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/windrush-compensation-scheme">completing our survey</a></p>
</div>

<h2 id="introduction-for-windrush-applicants">Introduction for Windrush applicants</h2>

<p>This information is for Commonwealth citizens and their children (the ‘Windrush generation’), and some other long term residents of the UK who do not have documents to demonstrate their status. The Windrush scheme explains the groups who are eligible and the documents they may receive.</p>

<p>The Windrush scheme started on 30 May 2018.</p>

<p>Applicants applying in the UK must apply using the paper application form (see above).</p>

<p>Applicants applying from overseas must apply using the <a rel="external" href="https://visas-immigration.service.gov.uk/apply-visa-type/windrush">online application form</a>.</p>

<p>The Windrush taskforce will contact postal and online applicants by phone or email if they need further information to decide their application.</p>

<div class="call-to-action">
<h3 id="contact-the-taskforce">Contact the taskforce</h3>

<p>Freephone: 0800 678 1925</p>

<p>Email: <a href="mailto:commonwealthtaskforce@homeoffice.gov.uk">commonwealthtaskforce@homeoffice.gov.uk</a></p>

<p>If you are overseas, you can email the taskforce and ask them to call you back.</p>

<p><a rel="external" href="https://gov.smartwebportal.co.uk/homeoffice/public/webform.asp?id=108&id2=A0BB64">Sign up for email updates</a> on:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Home Office announcements relating to Commonwealth citizens, including the Windrush generation</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>next steps for those affected, including the compensation scheme and lessons learned review</p>
  </li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2 id="compensation-scheme">Compensation scheme</h2>

<p>We are currently working to put in place a compensation scheme for Commonwealth citizens, including the Windrush generation, who have faced difficulties in establishing their status under the immigration system.</p>

<p>A public consultation on the design of the compensation is now open until 16 November. We will be announcing details of the final scheme and how to apply as soon as possible after the public consultation has ended.</p>

<p>Further information can be found on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/windrush-compensation-scheme">Windrush compensation scheme consultation page</a>.</p>

<h2 id="windrush-compensation-scheme-consultation-and-lessons-learned-review-roadshows">Windrush compensation scheme consultation and lessons learned review roadshows</h2>

<p>Wendy Williams and Martin Forde QC, independent advisers overseeing the lessons learned review and compensation scheme respectively, are hoping to meet with those impacted by measures designed for people who were in the country illegally and hear their personal accounts.</p>

<p>A series of events across England throughout September and October have been held to speak directly to people affected. <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/windrush-lessons-learned-review#windrush-lessons-learned-review-and-compensation-scheme-roadshows">Find out about venues and timings of the roadshows</a>.</p>

<h2 id="employers-and-landlords">Employers and landlords</h2>

<p>There is also guidance for <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/undocumented-commonwealth-citizens-resident-in-the-uk/guidance-for-landlords-conducting-right-to-rent-checks-on-undocumented-commonwealth-citizens">landlords</a> about right to rent checks and for <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/undocumented-commonwealth-citizens-resident-in-the-uk/guidance-for-employers-conducting-right-to-work-checks-on-undocumented-commonwealth-citizens">employers</a> on right to work checks on undocumented Commonwealth citizens.</p>

<h2 id="nhs-staff">NHS staff</h2>

<p>There is guidance for <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/windrush-generation-guidance-for-nhs-staff-and-nhs-care-providers">NHS staff and NHS care providers</a> on establishing entitlement to NHS-funded secondary care when patients are part of the Windrush generation or may not have immigration documents readily available.</p>
</div>
</div>

</div>

    </div>

